  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] war situation became more aggravated.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Everybody knew that the clouds, the war clouds, are gathering.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was on the-- it wasn't a question if.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The question was when it will break out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I returned to Bialystok, I suppose-- I don't know, the beginning of '39 or late in '38, because I finished in '37.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my ambitions-- of course, I was-- I was inclined to learn.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they were tempered with the reality of life, and not only the reality of life, as far as the family is concerned, but also with the reality of life in-- in Poland and in the world, because no one, at the age of 19, could close his eyes and say the whole world doesn't see us.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We knew that our youth is going to be challenged.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Our lives are going to be broken any day now.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in fact, for the last few years of that-- of that in our adolescent and early manhood, we never knew what youthful carelessness and freedom is, in this sense, because the weight of events and the weight of the situation-- the daily, the daily radio, the rantings and ravings of Hitler, and the things that were going on were part of our daily existence.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We waited for it, because we had to-- we had to understand and to appreciate how much closer we are getting to the moment of truth, in terms of unavoidable development of events.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And of course, Poland was the first victim.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The war started on the 1st of September, '39, in Poland.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
